The Commission of Inquiry into State Capture continues to hear Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (Prasa) related testimony by its Group Executive of Legal Risk and Compliance, Martha Ngoye. Video below:  Earlier, the Commission heard that the board of the Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (PRASA) went to great lengths to ensure that the company, Siyagena, linked to businessman Roy Moodley, got a contract worth billions of rands. PRASA Legal Risk and Compliance Group Executive Martha Ngoye told the Commission of irregularities and the forging of the signature of an executive, Tara Ngubane when phase one of the contract was drafted. 